---
source: tests/parity_help.rs
expression: stdout
---
aw - Manage isolated workspaces for AI agents

Usage:
  aw <command> [options]

Commands:
  init [base-name]        Initialize base workspace (default: 'default')
  create <name> [options] Create a new workspace from base
    --base <base-name>    Use specific base workspace (default: 'default')
  list                    List all workspaces
  open <name> [options]  Enter workspace (tmux session if available)
    --no-tmux             Open in a plain shell instead of tmux
  delete <name>           Delete a workspace
  config                  Show configuration file location
  edit-config             Open config file in default editor
  edit-base <base-name>   Open base workspace directory in editor
  sync                    Sync all repos in current workspace with remote
  open-home               Open tool home directory in editor
  help                    Show this help message

Environment Variables:
  AW_INSTALL_DIR              Tool home directory (default: ~/.agent-workspaces)
  AW_WORKSPACES_DIR    Where workspaces are created (default: ~/agent-workspaces)
  AW_CONFIG_FILE       Config file path (default: $AW_INSTALL_DIR/config.yaml)
  AW_BIN_DIR           Where 'aw' command is installed (default: ~/.local/bin)
